      <title>Woodworking History: Everything You Need to Know About Woodworking</title>
      <link>http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/woodworking-history-everything-you-need-to-know-about-woodworking/</link>
      <comments>http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/woodworking-history-everything-you-need-to-know-about-woodworking/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 31 May 2012 14:23:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>woodworkingman</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Woodworking]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds wood working]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds woodworking]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds woodworking review]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/woodworking-history-everything-you-need-to-know-about-woodworking/</guid>
      <description>A very popular hobby, woodworking is a craft that many become highly skilled at. Thousands of people have already honed their carpentry skills but there are so many more who are just now becoming interested in it. Being educated in the history of woodworking will not only help you appreciate it more, but can provide [...]&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://reviewtedswoodworking.com"&gt;Teds Woodworking Review -The Pros and Cons&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/teds-woodworking-review-the-pros-and-cons/Teds_Woodworking_Review_-The_Pros_and_Cons-Woodworking_History-_Everything_You_Need_to_Know_About_Woodworking.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A very popular hobby, woodworking is a craft that many become highly skilled at. Thousands of people have already honed their carpentry skills but there are so many more who are just now becoming interested in it. Being educated in the history of woodworking will not only help you appreciate it more, but can provide you with project ideas for yourself. Woodworking dates back much further than you might realize.</p>
<p> In fact even the first people on Earth, the most primitive human beings, are thought to have been involved in different forms of woodworking. Of course they didn’t have any of the fancy tools we have now, but they were able to make pots and plates out of wood and clay. Evidence has been found to support that a lot was build using wood back in those days. As time went on, their understanding of how to utilize wood continued to grow, as cave drawings showed Egyptians doing wooodworking projects.</p>
<p> During the time that the Great Pyramids were constructed, woodworkers of Egypt were incredibly accomplished and we see this in the magnificent structures that remain today. Because all the work was done by hand, even the most efficient workers still had to devote much more time towards finishing projects than we do today. Some of the best woodworkers in the early days included Evert Sodergren, Sam Maloof, Garrett Hack, Tage Frid, and Wharton Esherick.</p>
<p> While the principles of woodworking are not much different today than in the past, the primary difference is the technological advancement in supplies and tools. Primitive humans has very little to work with, whereas we have an abundance of power tools and wood that allow us to get projects done much more efficiently and precisely. In turn there are much more complex projects that can be completed and of course some woodworkers create huge buildings and log cabins in the middle of nowhere. You can make anything from wooden lawn figurines to kitchen cupboards, it all depends on the time and effort that you’re willing to put into it.</p>
<p> Today&#8217;s woodworkers should really take the time to appreciate the resources they have at their disposal compared to years past. If you want to get started in woodworking, once you’ve taken a look at the woodworking history you can appreciate the tools you’re using and learn the basics on how to read plans. Today&#8217;s tools are far more precise, which means that less skilled is required than ever before. There are even women now getting involved in woodworking and showing off their skills.</p>
<p><strong>Read More</strong>: <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/woodworking-plans/woodworking-bench-plans/">Woodworking Bench Plans</a>, <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/woodworking-reviews/teds-woodworking-review-the-pros-and-cons/" class="broken_link" rel="nofollow">Ted&#8217;s Woodworking Review</a>, <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/">Diy Woodworking</a></p>
<p></p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://reviewtedswoodworking.com">Teds Woodworking Review -The Pros and Cons</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
