      <link>http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/common-woodworking-supplies-what-to-buy/</link>
      <comments>http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/common-woodworking-supplies-what-to-buy/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 23 May 2012 16:55:54 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>woodworkingman</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Woodworking]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds wood working]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds woodworking]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[teds woodworking review]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://reviewtedswoodworking.com/common-woodworking-supplies-what-to-buy/</guid>
      <description>Woodworking is a hobby that can be a lot of fun. Whether you’re planning to get into it professionally or just have a bit of fun with it in your spare time, it’s important to purchase the proper woodworking supplies. For those who are just starting out, purchasing these supplies can be a bit overwhelming [...]&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://reviewtedswoodworking.com"&gt;Teds Woodworking Review -The Pros and Cons&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/teds-woodworking-review-the-pros-and-cons/Teds_Woodworking_Review_-The_Pros_and_Cons-Common_Woodworking_Supplies-_What_to_Buy.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Woodworking is a hobby that can be a lot of fun. Whether you’re planning to get into it professionally or just have a bit of fun with it in your spare time, it’s important to purchase the proper woodworking supplies. For those who are just starting out, purchasing these supplies can be a bit overwhelming at first. While many supplies are available, what you need to be concerned with at least initially are the essentials.</p>
<p> Some of these essentials are hand tools. Hammers, sandpaper, nails and wood glue are all basic supplies that are called for in almost all projects. You’re going to need some guides, jigs and stands. A jigsaw is a tool that is used to cut patterns in materials such as wood and metal.</p>
<p> For beginners, you might want to document each woodworking project in a book as you go. This way, you will have some projects to reference and to use as a guide; this is even common among professionals.</p>
<p> There are even online organizers to help you keep track of your plans so you can easily refer back to them in the future if you want. Additional lighting may be needed if you are going to work in a garage or a darker room</p>
<p> Of course there’s always the safety gear which is essential to have if you’re going to be doing any woodworking. This involves covering your mouth and nose with a dust mask and protecting your eyes with goggles. Safety gear prevents you from inhaling debris and dust. Hands should be protected with gloves, especially when using a saw.</p>
<p> Before shopping for woodworking supplies, make a list of everything you need first and get the highest quality you can afford. With woodworking, you will be much better off getting the best supplies. After you use your tools, clean them so they stay in good condition and continue to work efficiently. Buy need woodworking tools when necessary so you get the results you want and have more fun doing it.</p>
<p><strong>See Also:</strong> <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/woodworking-reviews/ted%E2%80%99s-woodworking-review-the-pros-and-cons/" class="broken_link" rel="nofollow">Ted’s Woodworking Review</a>, <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/woodworking-projects/woodworking-projects-for-beginners/">Woodworking Projects For Beginners</a>, <a href="http://www.doityourselfwoodworking.com/">DIY Woodworking</a></p>
<p></p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://reviewtedswoodworking.com">Teds Woodworking Review -The Pros and Cons</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
